    {
      "id": 348162,
      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "Gentiobiose, a rare disaccharide found in saffron and gentian, is a reducing sugar and forms only <small style=\"font-variant: small-caps\">D</small>-glucose on hydrolysis with aqueous acid. Reaction of gentiobiose with iodomethane and Ag<sub>2</sub>O yields an octamethyl derivative, which can be hydrolyzed with aqueous acid to give 1 equivalent of 2,3,4,6-tetra-<i>O</i>-methyl-<small style=\"font-variant: small-caps\">D</small>-glucopyranose and 1 equivalent of 2,3,4-tri-<i>O</i>-methyl-<small style=\"font-variant: small-caps\">D</small>-glucopyranose. If gentiobiose contains a <i>β</i>-glycoside link, what is its structure?",
